Article 4 
EPFL Direction Responsibilities 
1 The EPFL Direction has the following responsibilities: 
a. it adopts the ordinances, regulations and directives of the EPFL, subject to the delegations 
of authority provided for in this Ordinance;  
b. it adopts the rules and regulations concerning the organisation of EPFL Schools and 
College, particularly upon the proposal of the School Dean(s); 
c. it approves the creation or discontinuation of Institutes, Laboratories, Chairs, and Centres, 
particularly upon the proposal of the relevant School Dean(s); 
d. it approves the creation and abolition of academic curricula, particularly upon the proposal of 
the relevant School Dean(s);  
e. it takes decisions in its capacity as an employer on behalf of EPFL personnel, upon the 
proposal of the Vice-president for Human Development (VPH); 
f. it ensures the participation of social partners within the units for all general matters relating 
to personnel;  
g. it appoints the other members of the Directions of the Schools and College in accordance 
with the procedure defined under Art. 20 of this Ordinance;  
h.  it appoints Associate Vice-presidents upon the proposal of the Vice-president for Academic 
Affairs;  
i.  for each EPFL campus located outside the canton of Vaud, it appoints a Campus Committee 
upon the proposal of the Vice-president for Academic Affairs, and appoints a Director of 
Operations, upon the proposal of the Vice-president for Operations.  
j. it appoints the Vice Deans, as well as the Section, Institute and Centre Directors attached to 
the Schools upon the proposal of the relevant School Dean, and appoints the Directors of 
Doctoral programs  upon the proposal of the Vice-presidency for Academic Affairs;  
k. it decides on the launch and funding of transversal strategic projects;  
l. it adopts the Risk Profile and ensures the efficiency of the Internal Controls System;  
m. it is responsible for Quality Assurance;  
n. it promotes respect, diversity, fairness, and inclusion as fundamental values within the EPFL 
community;  
o. it exercises its responsibilities with due regard for overall sustainability objectives;  
p. it defines a set of organisational regulations; 
q. it defines the organisational structure of the Support Services to the EPFL missions. 
2 At regular intervals, based on the topics addressed, it delegates one of its members to meet with 
the EPFL Assembly (AE), as well as with representatives of relevant groups of people within the 
School as specified in article 17 of the Ordonnance sur l’EPFZ et l’EPFL, including, in particular, the 
members of the teaching staff (CCE), and the students (AGEPoly).

